	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Bregalad, did you actually read my review  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt=":roll:" title="Rolling Eyes" /> 
<br />
<br />FFIV hasn't been remade six times. The PS1 version was a direct port. The wonderswan conversion was an enhanced port, but still a port. The GBA version was a port of the Wonderswan version with some slight tweaks. On Wii it's only Virtual Console so that means a port of the SNES version. 
<br />
<br />There are only two remakes - the 3D rough polygon one on the DS and this "HD 2D" version on the PSP. 
<br />
<br />Two remakes of one of the bes classic RPGs of all time that are very different from each other isn't too much. The only thing I hope is that V and VI will receive the same treatment before PSP support dries up. I love IV don't get me wrong, but I feel it was bested by the other two 16-bit FFs to follow, especially VI.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
